  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for an ML surrogate model used for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML-augmented computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results are reported exclusively on a held-out test set drawn from the same distribution as the training corpus; no noise-injection, covariate-shift, or adversarial perturbation studies are included.",
