    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-ml-surrogate-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet their required levels at MRL 2. The ML surrogate achieves MAPE of 3.1% and R² = 0.974 on the nominal test set, and RH < 1.0 is satisfied at all five COU operating points. One informal out-of-distribution geometry evaluation yielded acceptable agreement, and the assessment team concluded that the model generalizes adequately for the intended COU. The six non-assessed factors are scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the Class II CPB device.",
